data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. WATERFRONT LIVING ON LAKE TARPON CANAL! Lake Tarpon awaits with this canal front, direct access to the lake, home in Palm Harbor! Fishing, skiing, boating and waterfront dining on Lake Tarpon’s 2500-acre Lake (largest in Pinellas County). This stunning 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom, 2 car garage home situated one from cul de sac offers commanding curb appeal. Enjoy extra space to store all your toys with an oversized cement driveway. You will be impressed as you enter the home with the open concept, split bedroom floorplan with high ceilings throughout. The family room/dining room combination have views of the double-sided wood burning fireplace. The kitchen boasts updated granite counters, wood cabinets, double oven/microwave, D/W and refrigerator. Large island offers stovetop with plenty of room for serving/entertaining guests. Tile backsplash and 18” tile on the floor. Light and bright eat in café area off kitchen with bank of windows offering water views. Master suite boast a huge walk-in closet, private bathroom with large shower. Bedrooms 2 & 3 are spacious with walk in closet and easy access to full bathroom in hall. The second bathroom is also accessible from the screened porch. Step outside to the screened porch to relax and enjoy the water views or boats meandering by. High ceilings throughout the home. Laundry room with washer/dryer included. A spacious 2 car garage and water softener offered as is. The backyard offers freshly laid grass and composite dock to park your boat/jet skis. Do not miss this incredible opportunity to embrace the waterfront lifestyle and enjoy the serenity and beauty of Lake Tarpon. Close to great shopping, museums, beaches, downtown Dunedin, and Tarpon Springs. John Chestnut and Anderson Parks are located right on the lake. Zoned for Palm Harbor Schools including Palm Harbor University High School. Optional HOA offers waterfront boat access and clubhouse. Flood Certificate and policy in attachments. Very low cost!
